Accident History
An RMP accident only covers those associated with material releases involved in the covered process and the regulated substance that is held above its threshold quantity. The release must also have caused off-site deaths, injuries, property damage, environmental damage, evacuations, or sheltering in place. All accident history reports shall include the following:
	Date and time of release;
	Chemical(s) involved in release;
	Quantity of chemical released;
	Description of release event;
	Release Source (i.e. process and equipment);
	Weather conditions at time of release;
	Description of on-site impacts associated with release;
	Initiating event causing the release (i.e. equipment failure, human error, over pressurization, etc.);
	Whether any off-site notifications were made; and
	Changes introduced as a result of the release.
Avanti has had no RMP incidents within the past 5 years. If such an event occurs it will be reported to the USEPA with an update to the RMP submission using RMP eSubmit within six months of the event.
